{"id":55653,"title":"[Acute blindness secondary to quinine toxicity: role of hyperbaric oxygen treatment].","abstract":"We report a rare case of quinine toxicity causing acute bilateral blindness, followed by documented partial recovery within 24 hours. The patient was treated with hyperbaric oxygenotherapy and intravenous nitrates. Visual defects persist after 6 months.","date":"2014-06-10","categories":"Eye Diseases","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24838026","annotations":[{"name":"Therapy","weight":0.750455,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Therapy"},{"name":"Oxygen","weight":0.729353,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Oxygen"},{"name":"Acute (medicine)","weight":0.673121,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_(medicine)"},{"name":"Intravenous therapy","weight":0.671518,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Intravenous_therapy"},{"name":"Toxicity","weight":0.660335,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toxicity"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.487328,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Hyperbaric medicine","weight":0.344956,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyperbaric_medicine"},{"name":"Blindness","weight":0.243787,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blindness"},{"name":"Quinine","weight":0.208635,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Quinine"},{"name":"Congenital disorder","weight":0.104746,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Congenital_disorder"},{"name":"Nitrate","weight":0.0537772,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nitrate"},{"name":"24 (TV series)","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/24_(TV_series)"},{"name":"Bilateralism","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bilateralism"},{"name":"Secondary school","weight":0.0147415,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Secondary_school"}]}
